Step 1. Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Identify Total Liabilities: From the balance sheet, the only liability is “Total Current Liabilities” with an End_amount of 1,015,922.54.  
• Total Assets (End_amount): 30,858,088.75.  
• Calculation:  
 Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 1,015,922.54 / 30,858,088.75  
  ≈ 0.0329, which rounds to 0.03  

Step 2. Gross Profit Margin  
• From the income statement:  
 Gross Profit = 5,718,450.67  
 Total Revenue = 20,318,450.67  
• Calculation:  
 Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (5,718,450.67 / 20,318,450.67) × 100  
  ≈ 28.13%  

Step 3. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement, “Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities” is –18,924,462.44.  
• From the balance sheet, “Total Current Liabilities” is 1,015,922.54.  
• Calculation:  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = –18,924,462.44 / 1,015,922.54  
  ≈ –18.63  

Thus, the solution is as follows:
  
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.03",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.13%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-18.63"
  }
}
